\q1
\v 18 Then \add вүҲat that time\add*, the mountains will drip sweet wine,
\q1 вүҲand the hills will flow with milk,
\q1 and all of Yehudah's streams will flow with water,
\q1 вүҲand a spring will go forth from Yahweh's residence and water the Shittim valley.
\b
\q1
\v 19 Egypt will become uninhabited,
\q1 and Edom will become a \add вүҲlonely\add* wilderness
\q1 because of the violence against the \add вүҲpeople\add* of YehudahвҖ”
\q1 they shed innocent blood in their \add вүҲcountry\add*.
\q1
\v 20 But Yehudah will remain forever,
\q1 and Yerushalem \add вүЎwill continue\add* \add вүҲthroughout the generations\add*,
\q1
\v 21 and I will \add вүҲdeclare their blood to be innocent (which I hadn't done previously)\add*,
\q1 because Yahweh resides in Tsiyyon.вҖқ
